Note:
C# to HIR Translation Test Suite

Tests: 10 test files covering C# → HIR translation for all major features
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_to_hir.runa" as ToHIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/file_io.runa" as File

@Reasoning:
Parses a C# source string into an AST through the real lexer -> parser
chain (create_csharp_lexer + create_csharp_parser + parse_program), the
same chain csharp_to_hir_from_source drives internally. Returns the AST
handle, or 0 on any failure, after tearing down the lexer and parser.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_csharp" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let source_length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let lexer be proc create_csharp_lexer from Lexer with source, source_length
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let parser be proc create_csharp_parser from Parser with lexer
    If parser is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_csharp_lexer from Lexer with lexer
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ast be proc parse_program from Parser with parser
    proc destroy_csharp_parser from Parser with parser
    proc destroy_csharp_lexer from Lexer with lexer
    Return ast
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared across the to_hir driver. Identical layout to
the parser and round-trip suites so a unified runner can consume any
of them without conversion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at offset 8, failed at offset 16; values are
mutated via Layout.memory_set_int64 since results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Drives the C# -> HIR half of the pipeline against the same 10 reference
programs the parser suite uses. Catches translator regressions that
would otherwise only surface as second-leg failures in the round-trip
suite, giving developers a cleaner signal of where a bug lives.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate TestResults, print header, call test_translation per program,
print_results, then return 1 if any test failed else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- basic_class.cs through namespaces_using.cs each parse and translate
  to a non-null HIR node carrying a non-zero node-type tag
- Missing file -> "Failed to read file" failure
- Parser regression on any program -> "Parse failed"
- Translator returns 0 on valid AST -> "Translation to HIR failed"
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/basic_class.cs", "Basic class", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/properties.cs", "Properties", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/lambda_expressions.cs", "Lambda expressions", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/generics.cs", "Generics", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/async_await.cs", "Async/await", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/events_delegates.cs", "Events and delegates", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/control_flow.cs", "Control flow", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/operators.cs", "Operators", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/nullable_types.cs", "Nullable types", results
    proc test_translation with "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/tests/csharp/programs/namespaces_using.cs", "Namespaces and using", results

    proc print_results with results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Five-stage verification for one C# source file: read, parse, allocate
arena, translate, and structural HIR check. Each stage that returns 0
fails the test with a distinct reason so the failure log identifies
exactly where in the C#-to-HIR pipeline the regression occurred.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Increment results.total.
2. read_entire_file(file_path) -> content; null: "Failed to read file".
3. parse_csharp(content) -> ast; null: free content, "Parse failed".
4. Allocate 64 KiB arena; null: free content, "Arena allocation failed".
5. translate_csharp_to_hir(ast, arena) -> hir; null: free content+arena,
   "Translation to HIR failed".
6. get_hir_node_type(hir) must be non-zero; otherwise free content+arena,
   "HIR node has no type tag".
7. Success: free content+arena, mark passed.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- programs/basic_class.cs -> reaches all 6 stages, results.passed += 1
- Non-existent path -> stage 2 fails with "Failed to read file"
- Malformed source -> stage 3 fails with "Parse failed"
- Translator returns 0 on valid AST -> stage 5 fails with "Translation to HIR failed"
- Translator returns an untyped node -> stage 6 fails with "HIR node has no type tag"
@End TestCases

Process called "test_translation" takes file_path as Integer, test_name as Integer, results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let content be proc read_entire_file from File with file_path

    If content is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Failed to read file"
        Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast be proc parse_csharp with content

    If ast is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Parse failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        Let _rfal2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal2 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let arena be proc allocate from Layout with 65536

    If arena is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Arena allocation failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        Let _rfal3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal3 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir be proc translate_csharp_to_hir from ToHIR with ast, arena

    If hir is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Translation to HIR failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        proc deallocate from Layout with arena
        Let _rfal4 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal4 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Verify the translation produced a structured HIR node by reading
    Note: its node-type tag through the real HIR accessor. Every node the
    Note: HIR builder emits carries a non-zero node_type; a zero tag means
    Note: the translator returned an unstructured/garbage handle.
    Let node_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir

    If node_type is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "HIR node has no type tag"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        proc deallocate from Layout with arena
        Let _rfal5 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal5 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    proc print_test_success with test_name
    proc deallocate from Layout with content
    proc deallocate from Layout with arena
    Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
One-time banner for the to-HIR suite. Rule width (35 "=") matches title
length so the heading boxes cleanly in CI logs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate title, print, deallocate; same for the "=" separator.
Always returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    proc print with "C# to HIR Translation Test Suite"
    proc print with "==================================="
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[PASS] <name>" line. Identical format to the other C# suites so unified
greps work across the suite.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[PASS] " prefix, print prefix and caller-owned test_name,
then deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_success" takes test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc print with "[PASS] "
    proc print with test_name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[FAIL] <name>: <reason>" line. reason indicates the stage that broke
(read, parse, arena, translate, HIR structure check) so failure logs
pinpoint exactly which to-HIR phase regressed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[FAIL] " prefix, print prefix, test_name, ": ", reason in
order, then deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_failure" takes test_name as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    proc print with "[FAIL] "
    proc print with test_name
    proc print with ": "
    proc print with reason
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block matching the parser/round-trip suites. Reads counters
through type-checked field access (results.total etc.) at the report
site for an extra exercise of struct access alongside the raw-offset
mutations inside test_translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print "=" separator, "Test Results:" heading, then Total/Passed/Failed
lines. Each label is allocated, printed, and deallocated; numbers go
through print_int.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    proc print with "==================================="
    proc print with "Test Results:"

    proc print with "Total: "
    proc print_int with results.total

    proc print with "Passed: "
    proc print_int with results.passed

    proc print with "Failed: "
    proc print_int with results.failed

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local integer printer (one per test file) so this layer of the
bootstrap has no dependency on stdlib formatting. Handles zero and
negative values directly with no reliance on a Long->String helper.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. value == 0 -> print "0" and return.
2. Allocate 32-byte buffer, walk position from 31 downward, writing
   ASCII digits (48 + temp % 10) right-to-left.
3. For negatives, operate on -temp during the loop, then write '-' (45)
   at the final position.
4. Bump position past the last decrement, print buffer+position as a
   zero-terminated C string, deallocate the buffer.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_int" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        proc print with "0"
        Return 1
    End If

    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    Note: Reserve the final byte as the NUL terminator so print reads a
    Note: bounded C string; digits are written from index 30 downward.
    proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, 31, 0
    Let position be 30
    Let temp be value

    If temp is less than 0:
        Set temp to -temp
    End If

    While temp is greater than 0:
        Let digit be temp modulo by 10
        Let char be 48 plus digit
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, char
        Set position to position minus 1
        Set temp to temp divided by 10
    End While

    If value is less than 0:
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, 45
        Set position to position minus 1
    End If

    Set position to position plus 1
    Let str_ptr be buffer plus position
    proc print with str_ptr

    proc deallocate from Layout with buffer

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of C# to HIR Translation Test Suite
